    <title>Combined summary - Base AMP</title>
    <updated>2023-05-25T16:47:58.222601+00:00</updated>
    <link href="https://lists.linuxfoundation.org/pipermail/lightning-dev/2018-November/001680.html" rel="alternate"/>
    <summary>Developers of the Lightning Network are currently discussing proposals for splitting and combining payments in the network. One proposal suggests adding an optional field to the invoice, while another proposes using a "max" value. They are also considering implementing an algorithm for executing a multipath payment with a divide and conquer scheme.Participants are proposing clarifications for Base AMP, which enables multiple partial payments to be combined into a single payment. For instance, they suggest verifying that receiving nodes can signal support for it and avoiding creating paths that need to be merged by intermediary nodes. The proposal for Base AMP includes a new type called `multipath_merge_per_hop`, indicating payment has been split and the receiver should wait for the total intended payment before forwarding or claiming it. However, Christian Decker disagreed with this proposal, citing added complexity and suggesting sticking with the simple mechanism of having the recipient be the only merge point. Developers also discussed handling partial payments in a network with multiple payment channels and the importance of sending the intended amount. They suggested having the flag included in invoices and not needing to be gossiped for simplicity and endpoint-only merging for reliability.ZmnSCPxj proposed an addition to the protocol to support Base AMP, including how to signal the awareness of a temporary underpayment with a single "more is coming"-bit. The email thread discusses the implementation of Base AMP, its opt-in process, and the various factors developers are considering such as complexity, reliability, and ease of implementation. Overall, developers are exploring different options and evaluating their feasibility to improve the Lightning Network's payment-splitting capabilities.</summary>
